  "question": "<p class=\"text--bold\" ng-bind-html=\"question.topQuestionText\">\n In the proof for the sum of squares, the inductive hypothesis for any natural number is:\n <br/>\n <br/>\n <i>\n  P\n </i>\n (\n <i>\n  n\n </i>\n ): 0\n <sup>\n  2\n </sup>\n + 1\n <sup>\n  2\n </sup>\n + 2\n <sup>\n  2\n </sup>\n + ... +\n <i>\n  n\n </i>\n <sup>\n  2\n </sup>\n =\n <i>\n  n\n </i>\n (\n <i>\n  n\n </i>\n + 1)(2\n <i>\n  n\n </i>\n + 1)/6,\n <i>\n  n\n </i>\n <span>\n  \u22650.\n </span>\n <br/>\n <br/>\n If\n <i>\n  n\n </i>\n = 0, then the left-hand side of\n <i>\n  P\n </i>\n (0) = 0\n <sup>\n  2\n </sup>\n = 0, and right-hand side of\n <i>\n  P\n </i>\n (0) = 0 \u00d7\u00a0(0 + 1)(2\u00a0\u00d7\u00a00 + 1)/6 = 0 .\n <br/>\n <br/>\n What is the right-hand side of\n <i>\n  P\n </i>\n (\n <i>\n  n\n </i>\n +1)?\n</p>\n",
